The divorce process in Trinidad and Tobago is relatively straightforward. The first step is to file a petition for divorce with the Family Court. The petition must be filed by the petitioner, who is the person who is seeking the divorce. The petitioner must be a resident of Trinidad and Tobago, and must be at least 18 years old. The petitioner must also be a citizen of Trinidad and Tobago, and must be at least 18 years old.
